                            <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/1">The book of Genesis, according to the Peshitta version.</title>
                            <rubric xml:lang="syr">
                                <title>ܒܪܝܬܐ ܣ̣ܦܪܐ ܩܕܡܝܐ ܕܐܘܪܝܬܐ</title>
                                <locus from="2b">2b</locus>
                            </rubric>
                            <note><p>The lessons are marked in the text in the usual way; others have been added subsequently at the top of the page.
                                The following portions of the text are wanting: ch. i. 7—18, ch. iii. 13—22, ch. v. 24—vi. 15, ch. xxii. 11—xxv. 17, and ch. xlvii. 13 to the end.</p></note>
                        </msItem>
                            <msItem n="2" xml:id="a2">
                                <locus from="1" to="2a">ff. 1-2a</locus>
                                <author key=""/>
                                <title>Index to additional lessons mentioned above.</title>
                                <rubric xml:lang="syr">
                                    <title></title>
                                    <note><p>܏ܩ ܕܚܡܫܐ ܒܫܒܐ ܕܐܢܝܚܬܐ ܏ܟـ ܝܓ ܏ܦ ܙ</p>
                                        <p>܏ܩ ܕܫܒܬܐ ܕܫܒܬܐ ܕܐܢܝܚܬܐ ܏ܟـ ܒ ܏ܦ ܒ</p>
                                        <p>܏ܩ ܕܚܕܒܫܒܐ ܚܕܬܐ ܪܝܫ ܟܬܒܐ</p>
                                        <p>܏ܩ ܕܚܕܒܫܒܐ :ܓ: ܡܢ ܩܝܡܬܐ ܏ܟـ ܐ ܏ܦ . .</p>
                                        <!--Note that the punctuation here does display in the right order from right to left but only in Author view not text view-->
                                        <p>܏ܩ ܕܚܕ ܒܫܒܐ : ܕ :܏ܟـ ܐ ܏ܦ ܚ</p>
                                        and so on. Here ܟـ stands for ܟܘܪܣܐ , % (quire), and ܦ for ܦܬܚܐ (opening).</note>
                                        <!-- Arabic needs to be added (noted on Word doc), we need a way to flag this in a tag? -->
                                        <locus from="1" to="2a">ff. 1-2a</locus>
                                </rubric>
